  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "\r\nTo improve the navigation experience on the different pages, the header and left navigation should be sticky to the browser window.\r\n\r\nThis is a design good practice that is used in almost all Devdocs websites.\r\n\r\nHeader: Add background color and make it fixed on desktop and mobile\r\n\r\nLeft Navigation: Add background color,  make it fixed on desktop and mobile, and add overflow to scroll when the content doesn't fit the screen vertically.\r\n\r\n\r\nUse-case example, using devtools in the browser to produce these screencasts\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1120748/208143113-5398b77d-0c09-442d-9db7-32b23f19f84a.mov\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1120748/208143251-f1f8f4c9-bd12-4b7c-b28c-e598918ce0b9.mov\r\n\r\n\r\ncautions to the top border on the left navigation\r\n![Screen Shot 2022-12-16 04 19 39 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1120748/208142638-7c42a9f8-0a80-4591-a2aa-0a8054729d9a.png)\r\n\r\nThe content going under the header is on purpose.\r\n![Screen Shot 2022-12-16 04 25 13 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1120748/208144245-8538c6fa-53f7-483b-808f-94b746474d42.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
